e information we are capable of obtaining collect information on your behalf help you gather your information review all information for accuracy and consistency coordinate communication of data to counsel review the final os for accuracy and consistency credit bond rating analysis and measurement we will conduct a detailed financial analysis of the client create a matrix to identify the client’s rating potential use the matrix to determine if a upgrade is possible use the matrix to develop a rating “plan” present the plan to the governing body credit rating preparation we will use the rating plan to develop a presentation strategy schedule practice meetings host each meeting identify participants needed in the presentation develop the presentation outline develop the presentation material “coach” the participants rehearse the presentation with you schedule the rating meeting handle all the travel arrangements allow for the safe transportation home interest rate investigations we will provide interest rate indications based on current markets provide interest rates for comparable bonds provide explanations of future rate trends selecting the most effective distribution process negotiated competitive bid private placement to a major purchaser private placement to a local bank private placement to the county comanaged with a local broker internal purchase general tax rate studies and millage estimates we will evaluate the best use of income taxes vs property taxes project revenue related to different tax streams determine how much each tax revenue can support calculate the tax rate to achieve the desired goals provide usable taxing options provide a calculator for bond millage rates provide a calculator for levy millage rates provide a table of the tax cost for residents debt limit verifications we will analyze all the factors impacting a client’s debt limits determine the client’s debt capacity affordability analysis we will analyze the project cost and available revenues identify alternative revenue sources determine the capital affordability determine the operating affordability recommend a structure that’s affordable creating debt policy we will get your current and future debt needs review the outstanding debt issues review the existing debt policy develop a policy for managing and issuing debt refine the outline into an actual debt policy confirming the sufficiency of current cash balances we will develop a balance sufficiency model create a stress test